article.headline: Navy 80, Lehigh 75
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Kaleo Kina scored 22 points to lead Navy to an 80-75 victory over Lehigh on Wednesday. Greg Sprink had 18 points, including 11 of 12 free-throw attempts, for Navy (12-12, 5-4 Patriot League), which won its fourth straight victory over Lehigh. Chris Harris had 12 points and Adam Teague added 10. Marquis Hall scored 22 of his 25 points in the second half for Lehigh (11-12, 4-5). Zahir Carrington scored 17 points, Rob Keefer had 10 points and Bryan White grabbed 10 rebounds. The two teams were tied 35-35 at the half and the lead changed hands 11 times in the second half. Fouls by Lehigh in the last two minutes allowed Sprink to get Navy a 74-71 lead with less than a minute to play. Hall's free throws cut the margin to one, but Sprink also made two with less than a second remaining to ice the win.
